sk of the slayer for instance.<br><br>since i got my ragebringer, i have obtained excactly one item with raw atk: a lodizal belt. i also have a goblin earring, but it doesn't stack with SoN. now, i'm far from end-game, but look at the equipment of top eq guilds' rogues, they have 2-3 atk items usually.<br><br>is this fair? i don't think so.... <p><font size="2" face="Arial"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=21797">Marauder Prodigious Prodigy</a><br>Fennin Ro</font><br><img src="http://prod.homepage.dk/pics/1106bs.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uarlinastarbright.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Arlina Starbright</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/2/02 5:53:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=24706.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Why do rogues/melee have to sacrifice stats for ATK?</span><hr size=1> Gloves I (enchanter) want, with and without FT:<br>Onyx Gauntlets - ac: 35  hp: 100  mana: 75  sv all: 3<br>Viscid Slime Gloves - ac: 13  str/wis/int: 8  hp: 50  mana: 50  sv all: 4<br><br>(relevant) Tradeoff from the non-ft gloves? ft+4  ac: -22  int: +8  mana: -25  hp: -50  sv all: +1<br><br><br>Collar I want, with and without FT:<br><br>Amulet of the Dreadgazer - ac: 15  str: 15  sta: 5  wis: 5  int: 10  HP: 75  Mana: 75  sv all: 10<br>Collar of Tavuel Xakreum - ac: 10  wis: 20  int: 10  hp: 60  fr: 15  mr: 20  ft2<br><br>(relevant) Tradeoff from the non-ft collar?  ft+2  ac: -5  sta: -5  hp: -15  mana: -75  fr: +5  mr: +10  cr/dr/pr: -10<br><br><br>Hat, with and without FT:<br><br>Crown of the Kromzek Kings - ac: 35  str: 10  wis: 10  int: 25  hp: 100  mr: +25  fr/cr/dr/pr: +10<br>Sage Headdress of Consciousness - ac: 10  str: 10  int: 25  mana: 100  ft1<br>Cursed Halo of Thought - stats/sv all: -5  ft3<br><br>Tradeoff from the non-ft crown?<br>either ft+1  ac: -25  hp: -100  mana: +100  mr: -25  fr/cr/dr/pr: -10<br>or ft+3  ac: -35  hp: -100  sta: -5  int: -25  mr: -25  fr/cr/dr/pr: -10<br><br><br>FT items aren't always superior to non-ft items. In fact, except possibly for the very very high-end luclin stuff I haven't considered, FT items are nearly always worse stat-wise than non-ft items, often considerably so.<br><br>Arlina <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uarlinastarbright.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Arlina Starbright</A> at: 8/2/02 5:54:25 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/upyneforrester.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Pyne Forrester</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/2/02 9:33:09 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=24706.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Why do rogues/melee have to sacrifice stats for ATK?</span><hr size=1> I tend to agree with Arlinna. <br><br>VI has made it an art in selecting gear for your toon. You gain AC to loose hp, a few more sv's and lower stats.<br><br>It is dissappointing to try and mate up all the best gear, when it does leave some areas lacking. <br><br>As a high end raiding rogue I would think ATK and stats/svs &gt; AC/HP. <br><br>As a druid I like FT, Mana and Sv itesm. I try not to get hit. HP would be the next stat I would look to improve. <p><ahref="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=216776">Pyne Forrester</a> <BR>"American Biker"  <BR><BR><ahref="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=216996">Leyta</a> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B